58
00:03:58,649 --> 00:04:01,861
Who's the big hot bag of air who
doesn't have to comb his hair...

59
00:04:01,986 --> 00:04:04,280
who doesn't bathe
and doesn't care?

60
00:04:04,405 --> 00:04:08,117
- Sanka! Sanka! Sanka!
- Yea, Sanka! Hey!

61
00:04:08,242 --> 00:04:10,119
What's happenin', star?
Where you been, man?

62
00:04:10,244 --> 00:04:14,080
You almost missed my all-time world
record: Seventh derby in a row.

63
00:04:14,205 --> 00:04:17,334
Easy, Rasta. I'm not going to forget
my best friend on this day of days.

64
00:04:17,459 --> 00:04:21,671
Derice, my grandfather says
you're definitely going to
make it to the Olympics.

65
00:04:21,796 --> 00:04:24,633
He says you're even faster
than your father.

66
00:04:24,758 --> 00:04:28,094
- Yeah, man, do it for Jamaica!
- Hey, you know what my grandfather says?

67
00:04:28,219 --> 00:04:30,388
- What?
- Get back to work!

68
00:04:30,513 --> 00:04:32,932
- Booie, booie!
- What are you talkin' about?

69
00:04:33,058 --> 00:04:35,935
Good luck, man. I'll see you
at the finish line, all right?

70
00:04:41,232 --> 00:04:43,443
- Hi, Momma Coffie.
- Hi, Derice.

71
00:04:43,568 --> 00:04:45,445
- Derice, is Sanka ready?
- Who knows?

72
00:04:45,570 --> 00:04:47,947
Ready. That boy's never ready.

73
00:04:48,073 --> 00:04:51,951
He's a lazy, crazy, sorry,
no-good bag of bones.

74
00:04:52,077 --> 00:04:54,287
So what you laughing at?

75
00:04:55,871 --> 00:04:58,582
All pushcarts
to the start position!

76
00:04:58,707 --> 00:05:01,335
- Ready, little man?
- Ready, big man.

77
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:03,337
Kiss the lucky egg.

78
00:05:04,797 --> 00:05:06,590
Let's go!

79
00:05:08,092 --> 00:05:11,595
- On your marks...
- Feel the rhythm! Feel the rhyme!

80
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,181
Get on up!
It's pushcart time!

81
00:05:14,306 --> 00:05:16,475
And go!

82
00:05:21,271 --> 00:05:24,608
Here we go, Winston!
The Rockett has been launched!

83
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:27,111
Hey, fruitcake!
Where'd you get that cart?

84
00:05:27,236 --> 00:05:30,114
Clear out!
Come on, move out! Look out!

85
00:05:32,074 --> 00:05:34,451
Sanka Coffie,
pushcart champion!

86
00:05:34,576 --> 00:05:37,537
- Pushcart champion!
- Get away! Get away!

87
00:05:37,662 --> 00:05:39,872
Hey, grandma, out of my way!

88
00:05:39,997 --> 00:05:45,336
Hey, Sunday driver, make room
for the Rasta Rockett! Make room!

89
00:05:45,461 --> 00:05:48,589
- Sanka, four more carts left!
- Pee Wee, move! Move out!

90
00:05:48,714 --> 00:05:52,844
I love Jamaica,
and Jamaica loves me!

91
00:05:52,969 --> 00:05:55,805
Champion! Champion!
You can't mess with the best!

92
00:05:55,930 --> 00:06:00,393
- Move over! Move over!
- Get away! Get off me!

93
00:06:00,518 --> 00:06:02,061
- Go, Sanka!
- Get him! Get him!

94
00:06:02,186 --> 00:06:05,565
One more cart left!
Go! Go! Go! Go!

95
00:06:05,690 --> 00:06:07,817
Yes! We win!

96
00:06:12,155 --> 00:06:14,031
Jump, Winston, jump!

97
00:06:22,164 --> 00:06:24,040
Sanka!

98
00:06:30,839 --> 00:06:33,175
Move it, man!
Move, move, move!

99
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:35,927
Sanka, you dead?

100
00:06:36,052 --> 00:06:37,929
Yeah, man.

101
00:06:43,101 --> 00:06:45,562
And where do you think
you're going?

102
00:06:45,687 --> 00:06:47,814
You caught me.

103
00:06:47,939 --> 00:06:51,401
- You have papers to grade.
- I'm just getting in one last run.

104
00:06:54,195 --> 00:06:57,073
I can't believe the tryouts
are finally here.

105
00:06:58,366 --> 00:07:01,452
- You nervous?
- I'm not nervous.

106
00:07:01,577 --> 00:07:05,789
I'm ready. I've been ready
for this day my whole life.

107
00:07:05,915 --> 00:07:10,002
I don't care how fast they run,
I'm going to run faster.

108
00:07:10,127 --> 00:07:14,506
I don't care how much
they want it, I want it more.

109
00:07:15,716 --> 00:07:17,593
I'm going to the Olympics, baby.

110
00:07:18,969 --> 00:07:22,348
I feel it.
I'm going to win the gold.

111
00:07:22,473 --> 00:07:26,352
Derice, are you nervous?

112
00:07:26,477 --> 00:07:28,354
I'm terrified.

113
00:07:34,109 --> 00:07:37,488
It's my turn, Joy!
It's my turn!

114
00:07:39,156 --> 00:07:42,492
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to the final event...

115
00:07:42,617 --> 00:07:44,410
of today's Olympic tryouts.

116
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:50,333
We have now come to the
main event of our games...

117
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:54,212
the running
of the 100-metre finals.

118
00:07:54,337 --> 00:07:56,714
We've had a most
successful afternoon...

119
00:07:56,839 --> 00:07:59,634
and I'd like to congratulate
all the athletes...

120
00:07:59,759 --> 00:08:02,762
who have participated
in today's events.

121
00:08:02,887 --> 00:08:06,474
- You sure no one can beat him?
- Oh, sure, I'm sure.

122
00:08:06,599 --> 00:08:08,810
I'm just a little concerned
about that big baldy.

123
00:08:14,774 --> 00:08:17,985
Let me first congratulate our athletes
on a splendid performance...

124
00:08:18,111 --> 00:08:21,614
and let me remind them that
only the top four finishers...

125
00:08:21,739 --> 00:08:27,452
will earn the right to represent
Jamaica in the forthcoming
summer games in Seoul, Korea.

126
00:08:27,577 --> 00:08:30,664
Wait. Y-You're Derice Bannock,
right?

127
00:08:30,789 --> 00:08:34,000
- That's me.
- Oh. I hope I make the team.

128
00:08:34,126 --> 00:08:39,589
- It would be a real honor to
run with you. Good luck to you.
- Good luck to you.

129
00:08:39,714 --> 00:08:43,051
Derice Bannock.
Hey, good luck to you too.

130
00:08:46,304 --> 00:08:49,015
Runners, take your marks.

131
00:08:59,943 --> 00:09:02,028
Get set!

132
00:09:47,071 --> 00:09:50,116
Mr. Coolidge, please,
you have to run the race over!

133
00:09:50,241 --> 00:09:52,744
I'm sorry, Derice.
Nothing can be done.

134
00:09:52,869 --> 00:09:54,829
But I was born to compete
in the Olympics!

135
00:09:54,954 --> 00:09:57,582
Then you're going to have to work
on your boxing or your cycling.

136
00:09:57,707 --> 00:10:00,418
Those are the only other two sports
in which Jamaica competes.

137
00:10:00,543 --> 00:10:03,463
I am not a boxer,
I am a runner.

138
00:10:03,588 --> 00:10:05,965
And it wasn't fair.

139
00:10:06,090 --> 00:10:09,427
It rarely is, my boy.
It rarely is.

140
00:10:13,097 --> 00:10:17,393
Well, Papa, what do I do now?

141
00:10:17,518 --> 00:10:21,856
Look, Derice, let it go, eh?
Let it go.

142
00:10:21,981 --> 00:10:24,651
You'll have another chance
in four years.

143
00:10:25,902 --> 00:10:27,778
Yeah.

144
00:10:29,863 --> 00:10:31,740
Mr. Coolidge...

145
00:10:31,865 --> 00:10:34,451
who is the other man in
the picture with my father?

146
00:10:34,576 --> 00:10:37,079
Irving Blitzer. He's an
American who lives here.

147
00:10:37,204 --> 00:10:40,791
- Unless, of course, he's
been arrested or shot.
- Excuse me?

148
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:42,876
Well, he's a bookie now.

149
00:10:43,001 --> 00:10:46,463
Takes his bets in a small
pool hall just past Sandy Bay.

150
00:10:46,588 --> 00:10:49,675
- Isn't that a gold medal
around his neck?
- Oh, yeah.

151
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:55,305
That lunatic was an Olympic
bobsledder who tried to get
your father to switch sports.

152
00:10:55,430 --> 00:10:59,976
He had some theory about using
track sprinters to push the bobsleds.

153
00:11:00,102 --> 00:11:02,604
Some ridiculous
thing like that.

154
00:11:02,729 --> 00:11:05,315
Can you imagine
a Jamaican bobsledder?

155
00:11:07,943 --> 00:11:10,820
And you're sure this man,
he lives on the island?

156
00:11:10,945 --> 00:11:12,988
- Oh, yes.
- Mr. Coolidge, thanks a lot.

157
00:11:13,114 --> 00:11:16,367
- Good, Derice.
- Oh, could I borrow this picture?

158
00:11:16,492 --> 00:11:20,663
- Bring it back!
- Yes, sir. Thanks a lot, Mr. Coolidge.

159
00:11:20,788 --> 00:11:24,208
- Oh, just one more thing.
- Mmm?

160
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:26,669
What's a bobsled?

161
00:11:28,254 --> 00:11:30,423
That's a bobsled.

162
00:11:30,548 --> 00:11:34,343
Oh. So a bobsled is
a pushcart with no wheels.

163
00:11:34,468 --> 00:11:37,513
- That's what it looks like here.
- Let me see that.

164
00:11:41,934 --> 00:11:45,229
All right. "The key elements
for a successful sled team...

165
00:11:45,354 --> 00:11:49,817
are a steady driver
and three strong runners
to push off down the ice."

166
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:53,153
Ice? Ice?

167
00:11:53,278 --> 00:11:55,155
Well...

168
00:11:56,781 --> 00:11:58,700
it's kind of a
winter sport, you know.

169
00:11:58,825 --> 00:12:02,871
- You mean winter, as in ice?
- Maybe.

170
00:12:02,996 --> 00:12:07,625
You mean winter, as in igloos
and Eskimos and penguins and ice?

171
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:10,336
- Possibly.
- See you.

172
00:12:10,462 --> 00:12:12,338
Where you going?

173
00:12:12,464 --> 00:12:15,425
I'm going to take a hot bath.
I'm getting cold just thinking
about all this ice.

174
00:12:15,550 --> 00:12:20,180
- No, man! You're going to be
part of my bobsled team!
- What do you need me for?

175
00:12:20,305 --> 00:12:24,726
Who is the best pushcart driver
in all o' Jamaica?

176
00:12:24,851 --> 00:12:26,728
- You're looking at him?
- Then you're going to do it?

177
00:12:26,853 --> 00:12:28,897
No!

178
00:12:29,022 --> 00:12:31,107
Hey, man, you could be famous.

179
00:12:31,232 --> 00:12:34,735
You could have your picture
on a Wheaties box.

180
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:38,864
But you said "no," and that's
all right, because I don't need you.

181
00:12:38,989 --> 00:12:42,409
Everybody is going to want
to be on my bobsled team!

182
00:12:42,534 --> 00:12:45,704
Look, star, let me tell you
a little something, all right?

183
00:12:45,829 --> 00:12:49,249
When you need something from me, you
don't have to hand me a bunch of lines.

184
00:12:49,374 --> 00:12:52,753
All you have to do is
look at me in the eye and say,
"Sanka, you are my best friend.

185
00:12:52,878 --> 00:12:56,089
We been through a whole heap together
and I really, really need you."

186
00:12:59,635 --> 00:13:03,013
Sanka, you're right.
And you are my best friend.

187
00:13:03,138 --> 00:13:05,849
- And we've been through
a whole lot together.
- Heap. Heap.

188
00:13:05,974 --> 00:13:08,810
Sorry, man.
Whole heap together.

189
00:13:08,936 --> 00:13:13,482
- "And I really, really need you."
- And I really, really need you.

190
00:13:13,607 --> 00:13:15,524
- Forget it.
- But you just said if I said that...

191
00:13:15,650 --> 00:13:19,528
All right.
All right, all right. All right, man.

192
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:22,907
So, let's talk about
this bill-sled team.

193
00:13:23,032 --> 00:13:25,743
- No, bobsled team.
- Whoever.

194
00:13:25,868 --> 00:13:29,622
Now, about the Wheaties box...
I'm going to be on it by myself, right?

195
00:13:29,747 --> 00:13:32,041
No, man, you're going to
be on it with me.

196
00:13:32,166 --> 00:13:34,543
And down the stretch they come!
Tumbleweed is holding on...

197
00:13:34,669 --> 00:13:36,921
- as Captain Video makes it
all the way on the outside.
- Yes, Tumbleweed, yes!

198
00:13:37,046 --> 00:13:39,423
- Come on! That's it!
- Brewster is dropping back
as Tumbleweed holds the rail.

199
00:13:39,548 --> 00:13:41,717
- Good Tumbleweed! Good Tumbleweed!
- And here comes Captain Video
on the outside!

200
00:13:41,842 --> 00:13:46,305
- Tumbleweed is slowing!
- No, Tumbleweed! No! Bad
Tumbleweed! What are you doing?

201
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:48,849
- Tumbleweed can't hold it and he
gets pinned against the rail.
- What? Don't do...

202
00:13:48,975 --> 00:13:51,018
- It's anyone's race
as they approach the rail!
- Don't do that! Let him out!

203
00:13:51,143 --> 00:13:53,354
- Captain Video makes his move!
Tumbleweed is running gamely...
- No! I need this one!

204
00:13:53,479 --> 00:13:55,981
- But Captain Video seems
just a little bit too strong!
- Please! Come on!

205
00:13:56,106 --> 00:13:57,983
- Here they come!
- No!

206
00:13:58,108 --> 00:14:01,152
Yes! Tumbleweed can't hold it,
as Captain Video takes charge.

207
00:14:01,277 --> 00:14:04,531
And it's Brewster finishing in second,
Susan's Pride finishes third...

208
00:14:04,656 --> 00:14:06,783
and Tumbleweed
is nowhere in sight!

209
00:14:06,908 --> 00:14:09,160
But, my, oh, my,
the odds-on favorite...

210
00:14:09,285 --> 00:14:11,830
- showed his true colors
with that late-stretch run.
- That's all right. Uh-huh.

211
00:14:11,955 --> 00:14:14,165
Tumbleweed held on momentarily,
but realistically...

212
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:16,376
only a fool would put
their money on Tumbleweed.

213
00:14:16,501 --> 00:14:18,378
That horse had no chance of...

214
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:25,927
That guy won two gold medals?

215
00:14:28,805 --> 00:14:30,390
I think so.

216
00:14:36,229 --> 00:14:38,522
That's Tumbleweed gone.

217
00:14:38,647 --> 00:14:40,399
Okay, next race.

218
00:14:43,777 --> 00:14:47,197
Excuse me. Are you
Mr. Irving Blitzer?

219
00:14:47,322 --> 00:14:49,533
Well, that depends
on who's asking.

220
00:14:49,658 --> 00:14:53,203
My name is Derice Bannock.
This is my teammate Sanka Coffie.

221
00:14:53,328 --> 00:14:55,581
Greetings, sled god.

222
00:14:55,706 --> 00:15:01,336
We were just wondering if you'd
be interested in coaching the
first Jamaican bobsled team.

223
00:15:02,755 --> 00:15:05,382
Derice, remember the radio?
Radio?

224
00:15:05,507 --> 00:15:08,427
Stick. Shooting with the stick.
Let's go!

225
00:15:08,552 --> 00:15:10,429
Let's go, Derice!

226
00:15:23,608 --> 00:15:25,943
Come on, Coach.

227
00:15:26,068 --> 00:15:27,945
Just help me get started!

228
00:15:41,042 --> 00:15:42,919
- Greetings, sled god.
- Sorry to bother you...

229
00:15:43,044 --> 00:15:45,379
- Get out! Get out!
- But you're the only one
that can help us!

230
00:15:54,472 --> 00:15:56,641
- Go away.
- Okay.

231
00:15:57,850 --> 00:16:00,102
Nice to meet you!

232
00:16:00,228 --> 00:16:03,355
- Maybe today is a bad day.
- Yeah.

233
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:07,442
I'll come back tomorrow, and
the next day, and the next day,

234
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:09,444
- No. No!
- And the next day.

235
00:16:09,569 --> 00:16:11,988
- Look, whatever you're name is...
- Derice.

236
00:16:12,113 --> 00:16:15,533
All right, Derice, let me lay
out some difficulties for you.

237
00:16:15,659 --> 00:16:17,869
Snow... you don't have any.

238
00:16:17,994 --> 00:16:20,247
It's 900 degrees out there.

239
00:16:20,372 --> 00:16:22,249
Time... you don't have any.

240
00:16:22,374 --> 00:16:24,459
The Olympics
are in three months.

241
00:16:24,584 --> 00:16:27,754
And me... you don't have me.

242
00:16:27,879 --> 00:16:31,258
As far as I'm concerned, the sport
of bobsledding no longer exists.

243
00:16:31,383 --> 00:16:33,843
I don't want to do it,
I don't want to coach it...

244
00:16:33,969 --> 00:16:37,097
and most of all...
and I mean most of all...

245
00:16:37,222 --> 00:16:41,476
I don't want to be within
2,000 miles of anyone who does.

246
00:16:41,601 --> 00:16:46,146
- Now, did you follow all that?
- Then how come you still have
that poster on the wall?

247
00:16:48,774 --> 00:16:50,651
Is that what's bothering you?

248
00:16:54,655 --> 00:16:57,491
There. Is that better?

249
00:16:57,616 --> 00:16:59,493
Are you happy?

250
00:17:06,458 --> 00:17:10,504
Like I said,
my name is Derice Bannock.

251
00:17:10,629 --> 00:17:12,631
I'm Ben Bannock's son.

252
00:17:17,177 --> 00:17:20,681
I haven't seen this picture
in twenty years.

253
00:17:20,806 --> 00:17:22,850
Huh! Would you look at me then.

254
00:17:24,934 --> 00:17:30,314
- Ooh. Would you look at me now?
- Please, Mr. Blitzer.

255
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:32,066
Just give me a chance.

256
00:17:32,191 --> 00:17:34,152
If I don't have what it takes,
we forget the whole thing.

257
00:17:34,277 --> 00:17:39,323
- Believe me, kid, you do not
have what it takes.
- But you thought my father did.

258
00:17:39,449 --> 00:17:44,036
Your father was one of
the toughest competitors I ever saw.

259
00:17:44,162 --> 00:17:46,998
He ran the 100 meters
in ten-flat.

260
00:17:47,123 --> 00:17:49,041
Well, I run it in 9.9.

261
00:17:52,503 --> 00:17:55,590
Come on. Coach me.

262
00:17:57,759 --> 00:18:01,804
Sorry. You're a couple
decades late.

263
00:18:01,929 --> 00:18:04,223
Oh, I see. Well, it might be
easy for you...

264
00:18:04,348 --> 00:18:06,224
to walk away from me,
Mr. Blitzer...

265
00:18:06,349 --> 00:18:08,226
but you can't walk away
from this:

266
00:18:08,351 --> 00:18:11,146
20 years ago you came down here
to see if you could make...

267
00:18:11,271 --> 00:18:13,440
a Jamaican sprinter
into a bobsledder...

268
00:18:13,565 --> 00:18:15,901
and you never got that chance.

269
00:18:16,026 --> 00:18:18,111
Look at me, Mr. Blitzer.

270
00:18:18,236 --> 00:18:20,113
I'm your chance.

271
00:18:20,238 --> 00:18:22,282
Take it.

272
00:18:33,502 --> 00:18:35,795
All right, everyone quiet down.

273
00:18:35,921 --> 00:18:37,881
Nice group here.

274
00:18:38,006 --> 00:18:41,593
Now, for two of you lucky people,
our trip to the Olympics...

275
00:18:41,718 --> 00:18:43,595
starts right now.

276
00:18:44,971 --> 00:18:46,932
And I want to introduce you...

277
00:18:47,056 --> 00:18:49,225
to Mr. Irving Blitzer...

278
00:18:49,350 --> 00:18:52,770
who's going to be
our expert bobsled coach.

279
00:18:54,396 --> 00:18:56,815
Sanka, hit it, man.

280
00:18:56,941 --> 00:18:59,318
You're on the air, sled god!

281
00:19:02,446 --> 00:19:06,784
- Gentlemen, a bobsled
is a simple thing.
- Yeah! So's a toilet!

282
00:19:09,245 --> 00:19:12,164
Thank you.
Thank you very much.

283
00:19:12,289 --> 00:19:15,125
Basically, what you're looking to do
is get your sorry rear ends...

284
00:19:15,251 --> 00:19:18,921
from the top of an icy chute
to the bottom.

285
00:19:19,046 --> 00:19:22,299
You're ziggin',
you're zaggin'.

286
00:19:22,424 --> 00:19:26,595
It's the biggest, coldest roller
coaster you've ever been on.

287
00:19:28,389 --> 00:19:30,306
I-Ice.

288
00:19:35,937 --> 00:19:37,689
Oh, yeah.

289
00:19:37,814 --> 00:19:40,108
Oh, yeah.

290
00:19:40,233 --> 00:19:42,193
I almost forgot, uh...

291
00:19:42,318 --> 00:19:45,196
One minor drawback to this
delightful winter sport...

292
00:19:45,321 --> 00:19:48,116
is the high-speed crash.

293
00:19:48,241 --> 00:19:50,368
That hurt. Aah.

294
00:19:50,493 --> 00:19:54,914
Always remember, your bones
will not break in a bobsled.

295
00:19:55,039 --> 00:19:57,041
No, no. They shatter.

296
00:20:04,090 --> 00:20:06,050
So...

297
00:20:06,175 --> 00:20:08,052
who wants in?

298
00:20:22,024 --> 00:20:23,900
Look, Baldy's here.

299
00:20:26,319 --> 00:20:30,741
- Glad you could make it, man!
- Don't touch me!

300
00:20:30,866 --> 00:20:34,036
No problem. So what's your name?

301
00:20:34,161 --> 00:20:36,038
Yul Brenner.

302
00:20:39,207 --> 00:20:42,711
Well, it's good to have you
as a teammate, Brenner.

303
00:20:42,836 --> 00:20:45,547
Let's get one thing straight,
Bannock.

304
00:20:45,672 --> 00:20:47,924
We may be on the same team...

305
00:20:48,050 --> 00:20:50,343
but I am no one's teammate.

306
00:20:50,469 --> 00:20:52,970
- Long as you come here to bobsled.
- Hey, listen, man...

307
00:20:53,095 --> 00:20:55,264
the only reason why
I come here...

308
00:20:55,389 --> 00:20:58,893
is to get off of this
stinkin' island.

309
00:20:59,018 --> 00:21:01,896
If I have to take one
of those bobsleds to do it...

310
00:21:02,021 --> 00:21:04,065
then all right.

311
00:21:04,190 --> 00:21:07,067
- No problem.
- Uh, yes.

312
00:21:07,193 --> 00:21:11,405
Yes, I have a problem. There's
no such thing as a three-man sled.

313
00:21:11,530 --> 00:21:14,658
- You're one Jamaican short.
- Hey.

314
00:21:17,203 --> 00:21:19,789
The meeting start yet?

315
00:21:19,914 --> 00:21:21,791
- Uh-oh.
- You!

316
00:21:21,916 --> 00:21:25,628
- I'll kill you.
College boy, I'll kill you!
- Wait! Hold on!

317
00:21:25,753 --> 00:21:28,756
- Hey, hey! Lighten up!
Whoa! Whoa! Down, boy!
- Wait a second!

318
00:21:28,881 --> 00:21:32,259
- He didn't mean anything!
He didn't mean it!
- You're dead! You're dead!

319
00:21:32,384 --> 00:21:35,261
Kill him,
and we don't have a team.

320
00:21:35,386 --> 00:21:39,224
- I'm not riding
in the same sled as that.
- He tripped me too, you know.

321
00:21:39,349 --> 00:21:43,102
But in case you haven't noticed,
there's no one else here.

322
00:21:43,228 --> 00:21:45,980
You're crowding me, slinky head.

323
00:21:46,105 --> 00:21:48,107
Slinky head.
That's a good one.

324
00:21:48,233 --> 00:21:50,610
- What are you laughing about?
- Nothing.

325
00:21:50,735 --> 00:21:55,073
If it wasn't for you, rich boy,
I'd be in the Olympics right now.

326
00:21:55,198 --> 00:21:57,075
I don't know what
you all are arguing about...

327
00:21:57,200 --> 00:22:01,371
- 'cause Derice was going to
beat both your butts anyway.
- What are you talking about?

328
00:22:01,496 --> 00:22:03,414
How 'bout I beat your butt
right now?

329
00:22:03,540 --> 00:22:06,793
How 'bout I draw a line down the middle
of your head so it looks like a butt?

330
00:22:13,258 --> 00:22:15,551
Forget it, man. I'm gone.

331
00:22:15,676 --> 00:22:19,972
Fine. Stay here on the island.
We're going to Canada.

332
00:22:25,102 --> 00:22:27,062
All right.

333
00:22:27,187 --> 00:22:29,273
I'll do it.

334
00:22:29,398 --> 00:22:33,151
But you'd better tell
this mama's boy...

335
00:22:33,277 --> 00:22:35,571
to stay the hell
away from me.

336
00:22:35,696 --> 00:22:38,115
You understand?

337
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:40,117
No problem.

338
00:22:41,451 --> 00:22:43,328
Hey, Irv...

339
00:22:43,453 --> 00:22:48,083
say hello to the first
Jamaican bobsled team.

340
00:22:55,215 --> 00:22:57,091
Oh, goody.

341
00:22:59,051 --> 00:23:02,972
Gentlemen, this is a bobsled.

342
00:23:03,097 --> 00:23:05,141
Sort of.

343
00:23:05,266 --> 00:23:08,602
- All right, here's what
we're going to do. Yul...
- Don't touch me.

344
00:23:08,728 --> 00:23:12,690
Of course. Sorry. You're going
to be the second middle man.

345
00:23:12,815 --> 00:23:16,277
You're strong, you're fast, and
you're going to love that seat.

346
00:23:16,402 --> 00:23:18,904
Junior, you're the first
middle man.

347
00:23:19,030 --> 00:23:22,074
You're quick, you're sharp.
Hop in.

348
00:23:22,199 --> 00:23:24,243
- Sanka...
- I know... I'm the driver, right?

349
00:23:24,368 --> 00:23:27,371
- No, you're the brake man.
- No... No, I'm the driver.

350
00:23:27,496 --> 00:23:30,207
No, you're not.
You're the brake man.

351
00:23:30,333 --> 00:23:33,586
- I'm the driver.
- You're not! You're the brake man.

352
00:23:33,711 --> 00:23:35,671
See, you don't understand!
I am Sanka Coffie!

353
00:23:35,796 --> 00:23:38,339
I'm the best pushcart driver
in all of Jamaica!

354
00:23:38,465 --> 00:23:41,926
I must drive! Do you dig
where I'm coming from?

355
00:23:42,052 --> 00:23:43,928
- Yeah, I dig where you're coming from.
- Good.

356
00:23:44,054 --> 00:23:47,223
Now dig where I'm coming from.
I'm coming from two gold medals.

357
00:23:47,348 --> 00:23:50,810
I'm coming from nine world records
in both the two and four-man events.

358
00:23:50,935 --> 00:23:55,774
I'm coming from ten years of
intense competition with the
best athletes in the world.

359
00:23:55,899 --> 00:23:58,151
That's a hell of a place
to be coming from.

360
00:23:58,276 --> 00:24:01,863
You see, Sanka, the driver
has to work harder than anyone.

361
00:24:01,988 --> 00:24:04,908
He's the first to show up
and the last to leave.

362
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:09,704
When his teammates are all out
drinking beer, he's up in his
room studying pictures of turns.

363
00:24:09,829 --> 00:24:14,459
You see, a driver must remain focused
one hundred percent at all times.

364
00:24:14,584 --> 00:24:18,463
Not only is he responsible for knowing
every inch of every course he races...

365
00:24:18,588 --> 00:24:22,091
he's also responsible for the lives
of the other three people in his sled.

366
00:24:24,384 --> 00:24:26,261
Now, do you want
that responsibility?

367
00:24:26,386 --> 00:24:28,847
I say we make Derice
the driver.

368
00:24:28,972 --> 00:24:31,934
So do I, Sanka, so do I.

369
00:24:36,522 --> 00:24:39,149
Oh, the back is nice.

370
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:42,820
All right, Father, listen here.

371
00:24:42,945 --> 00:24:46,573
You see, I've made up my mind.
I'm going to be a bobsledder.

372
00:24:47,908 --> 00:24:50,994
That's right. A bobsledder.

373
00:24:52,412 --> 00:24:54,289
Oh, really?

374
00:24:54,414 --> 00:24:57,543
Well, I'm sorry
you feel that way.

375
00:24:57,668 --> 00:25:00,671
Fine. Cut off my allowance.

376
00:25:00,796 --> 00:25:03,130
Because you see, Father...

377
00:25:03,256 --> 00:25:07,510
a man has got to do
what a man has got to do.

378
00:25:18,020 --> 00:25:20,147
Just who I wanted to see.

379
00:25:20,273 --> 00:25:24,652
- M-M-Me?
- You know where I just came from?

380
00:25:24,777 --> 00:25:28,322
- W-Where?
- I got you a job...

381
00:25:28,447 --> 00:25:33,619
with Webster, Webster and Cohen,
the biggest brokerage house in Miami!

382
00:25:33,744 --> 00:25:37,456
- Oh, right. Webster, Webster and Cohen.
- Yes! That's right.

383
00:25:37,582 --> 00:25:40,334
And you start end of the month.

384
00:25:42,962 --> 00:25:45,839
- Yes, but I thought that I would...
- Look...

385
00:25:45,964 --> 00:25:49,801
we went along with this
track nonsense long enough.

386
00:25:49,926 --> 00:25:54,973
And we agreed that it's time to
get on with your real future. Right?

387
00:25:56,474 --> 00:25:59,311
- I know...
- Right?

388
00:25:59,436 --> 00:26:01,896
- Yes, sir.
- Good.

389
00:26:05,525 --> 00:26:07,736
I'm going to tell your mother.

390
00:26:18,913 --> 00:26:21,166
I guess we sure told him.

391
00:26:24,002 --> 00:26:28,839
Winning a bobsled race
is about one thing: The push start.

392
00:26:28,964 --> 00:26:32,343
Now, I know you dainty little
track stars think you're fast.

393
00:26:32,468 --> 00:26:35,012
Well, heh, let's see
how fast you are...

394
00:26:35,137 --> 00:26:38,432
when you push
a 600-pound sled.

395
00:26:38,557 --> 00:26:42,269
Now, a respectable start time
is 5.7 seconds.

396
00:26:42,394 --> 00:26:45,397
If you speed demons can't
whip off an even six-flat...

397
00:26:45,522 --> 00:26:48,567
you have a better chance of
becoming a barbershop quartet.

398
00:26:50,194 --> 00:26:52,529
Derice, come on! Hey!

399
00:26:52,654 --> 00:26:55,032
Junior, get in! Never mind!

400
00:26:57,242 --> 00:26:59,912
We'll have to move it back.
Let's go!

401
00:27:00,037 --> 00:27:04,750
- Here on this mountain top Whoa-oh
- Slow down! What are you
doing to me? Slow down!

402
00:27:04,875 --> 00:27:07,418
- I got some wild, wild life
- 14.3. No good.

403
00:27:07,543 --> 00:27:10,588
- I've got some bills
to pay, whoa-oh
- 13.5. 11.7.

404
00:27:10,713 --> 00:27:13,466
This is what it's all about!
This is where you win or lose the race!

405
00:27:13,591 --> 00:27:16,135
Right here in the pushcart! This
is where you're gonna practice!

406
00:27:16,260 --> 00:27:18,638
Right here! Right here in the
Volkswagen, you're gonna practice!

407
00:27:18,763 --> 00:27:22,308
No, Junior, quit falling down!
Come on, hustle!

408
00:27:22,433 --> 00:27:24,644
Catch up to them!
There you go!

409
00:27:24,769 --> 00:27:27,897
Junior! No! Do it again!

410
00:27:28,022 --> 00:27:31,484
Whoa, whoa! Stop! Stop, Derice!
Stop! Wait! Wait for me!

411
00:27:31,609 --> 00:27:34,487
Wait! I'm in! Stop!
Slow down!

412
00:27:37,573 --> 00:27:42,120
- Great. Very good. Try it again.
- Wild, wild life

413
00:27:42,245 --> 00:27:45,832
If I've said it once,
I've said it 46 times.

414
00:27:45,957 --> 00:27:49,501
Cold weather endurance is vital
to building a successful sled team.

415
00:27:52,921 --> 00:27:56,132
- Cold enough?
- Wild, wild life

416
00:27:56,258 --> 00:28:00,887
- You got to live your life
You got to live your life
- One, two, three!

417
00:28:01,012 --> 00:28:03,473
Wild, wild life

418
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:10,146
- Wild, wild life
- Go! Go! Go!

419
00:28:16,778 --> 00:28:19,906
- Here on this mountain top Whoa-oh
- Whoa! Slow down!

420
00:28:20,031 --> 00:28:23,493
- Sanka, hit the brakes!
Hit the brakes, man!
- I can't! It's stuck!

421
00:28:23,618 --> 00:28:24,828
Hold on!

422
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:31,208
About some wild, wild life

423
00:28:43,345 --> 00:28:46,223
Sanka, you dead?

424
00:28:46,348 --> 00:28:47,975
Yeah, man.

425
00:28:50,102 --> 00:28:54,148
What have you done to the
police unit? I shall arrest you!

426
00:28:54,273 --> 00:28:57,693
- Who owns this thing?
- We do, sir.

427
00:28:57,818 --> 00:29:01,697
- And who are you?
- The Jamaican bobsled team, sir.

428
00:29:06,327 --> 00:29:08,996
Don't give me that business.
I wasn't born yesterday.

429
00:29:09,121 --> 00:29:12,040
5.9! 5.9!
You did it! You did it!

430
00:29:12,165 --> 00:29:15,501
5.9! We did it!
We did it! 5.9!

431
00:29:15,627 --> 00:29:19,213
Get out of the way. Get out
of the way. 5.9, guys. What?

432
00:29:19,339 --> 00:29:22,216
- Who are you?
- I'm their coach! You guys okay?

433
00:29:22,342 --> 00:29:23,843
- Yeah.
- Yeah.
- How's the sled?

434
00:29:23,968 --> 00:29:26,179
- Yeah, man, we're fine.
- Sled's okay?

435
00:29:26,304 --> 00:29:28,181
Well, it's in the wrong place!
Get it back to the top of the hill!

436
00:29:28,306 --> 00:29:31,225
Let's move it right now, you slackers!
Move it! Let's hustle! Come on!

437
00:29:31,351 --> 00:29:34,062
Let's move it!
Come on, you guys! Move it!

438
00:29:35,855 --> 00:29:38,900
I'm not asking for
a winter sports programme.

439
00:29:39,025 --> 00:29:43,613
All I need is a lousy 20 grand so I can
get us to the Olympics. That's all.

440
00:29:43,738 --> 00:29:46,532
How in God's name are you
going to get to the Olympics?

441
00:29:46,657 --> 00:29:49,077
These boys have never even
seen a sled race before!

442
00:29:49,202 --> 00:29:53,121
Mr. Coolidge, I have been looking at
sledders since I was twelve years old.

443
00:29:53,246 --> 00:29:57,084
If I say these kids can make it
to the Olympics, they can make
it to the Olympics.

444
00:29:57,209 --> 00:30:00,629
Okay. Well, I'll tell you
what we'll do.

445
00:30:00,754 --> 00:30:04,633
Practice down here with
the boys a bit more, and when
you're a little further along...

446
00:30:04,758 --> 00:30:07,427
- I'll come along and see you...
- No! No! No!

447
00:30:07,552 --> 00:30:10,389
Now, just a minute,
Mr. Blitzer.

448
00:30:10,514 --> 00:30:12,933
This country enjoys
a fine athletic tradition...

449
00:30:13,058 --> 00:30:15,394
and if you think I'm going to give you
the little money we have...

450
00:30:15,519 --> 00:30:18,980
so that you can parade us around in
front of the world like a freak show...

451
00:30:19,106 --> 00:30:20,982
you've got another thing coming.

452
00:30:21,108 --> 00:30:24,152
It's bad enough how you
embarrassed your own country.

453
00:30:24,277 --> 00:30:26,655
I'm certainly not going to
allow you to embarrass ours.

454
00:30:29,241 --> 00:30:31,118
No go, kid.

455
00:30:32,744 --> 00:30:34,954
That's okay, Coach.
We'll get the money.

456
00:30:35,079 --> 00:30:38,582
- Do the words "give up"
mean anything to you?
- Not a thing.

457
00:30:40,209 --> 00:30:43,003
Some people say you know
they can't believe

458
00:30:43,129 --> 00:30:45,464
Jamaica
We have a bobsled team

459
00:30:45,589 --> 00:30:48,759
'Nuff people say you know
they can't believe

460
00:30:48,884 --> 00:30:51,095
Jamaica
We have a bobsled team

461
00:30:51,220 --> 00:30:55,641
Hi. I'm here to offer you an
opportunity of a lifetime.

462
00:30:55,766 --> 00:30:58,978
We're looking for a sponsor
for the first Jamaican bobsled team.

463
00:32:20,932 --> 00:32:22,809
Oh!

464
00:32:26,647 --> 00:32:30,067
We have the one Derice
and the one Junior

465
00:32:30,192 --> 00:32:33,236
I'll pay you a dollar
to shut up!

466
00:32:37,032 --> 00:32:41,827
We got nine dollars and fifty-two cents
from Yul Brenner, thank you.

467
00:32:41,952 --> 00:32:44,455
We got a hundred and eighty-four
dollars from Derice and me.

468
00:32:44,580 --> 00:32:47,458
Sanka, how did your singing
on the street go?

469
00:32:49,543 --> 00:32:51,712
How did it go?

470
00:32:51,837 --> 00:32:53,714
It went like this:

471
00:32:53,839 --> 00:32:55,966
'Nuff people say you know
they can't believe

472
00:32:56,092 --> 00:32:58,260
- Sanka, we know.
- Jamaica, we have a bobsled team

473
00:32:58,386 --> 00:32:59,762
- Sanka.
- We have the one Derice...

474
00:32:59,887 --> 00:33:02,765
How much?

475
00:33:02,890 --> 00:33:06,227
- I made a dollar and sixteen cents.
- Oh, that's great.

476
00:33:06,352 --> 00:33:08,896
We're only short about
nineteen thousand bucks.

477
00:33:09,021 --> 00:33:11,440
- Sorry I'm late, everybody.
- No, really, that is terrific.

478
00:33:11,565 --> 00:33:14,735
Don't pack a suitcase, Junior.
We're not going.

479
00:33:15,861 --> 00:33:17,738
Mmm, that's too bad.

480
00:33:21,825 --> 00:33:24,828
- Whoa!
- Oh! Where'd you get it, man?

481
00:33:24,953 --> 00:33:28,915
- I sold my car.
- Yes, man.

482
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:31,918
- I am going.
- No, we're not.

483
00:33:32,043 --> 00:33:35,004
Look here, Junior, I appreciate
what you're trying to do here...

484
00:33:35,130 --> 00:33:37,966
but we can't accept this money;
it just wouldn't be proper.

485
00:33:38,091 --> 00:33:41,094
Uh, Derice, if I hadn't
tripped you fellas...

486
00:33:41,219 --> 00:33:45,473
we'd already have been going
to the Olympics; I want you to have it.

487
00:33:51,437 --> 00:33:53,815
You mean you want us
to have it, right?

488
00:33:53,940 --> 00:33:56,025
Right. Us.

489
00:33:58,236 --> 00:34:00,864
Thanks a lot, Junior.
Thanks a whole heap, man.

490
00:34:00,989 --> 00:34:06,034
Remember, this doesn't mean
that I like you, you understand?

491
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:10,330
Be sure to thank your father for
us, 'cause Lord knows, he didn't
have to let you sell that car.

492
00:34:10,455 --> 00:34:13,208
Well, uh, he doesn't know
I sold the car.

493
00:34:13,333 --> 00:34:17,588
Um, he doesn't know
I'm on the team.

494
00:34:17,713 --> 00:34:20,132
He thinks I'm off to Miami...

495
00:34:20,257 --> 00:34:22,134
and I loaned the car
to a friend...

496
00:34:22,259 --> 00:34:26,346
to work for Webster, Webster
and Cohen, someplace like that.

497
00:34:27,806 --> 00:34:30,434
Some people say you know
them can't believe

498
00:34:30,559 --> 00:34:32,519
Jamaica
We have a bobsled team

499
00:34:32,644 --> 00:34:35,898
- Yes!
- We have the one Derice
- And the one Junior

500
00:34:36,023 --> 00:34:38,025
Yu... Sanka

501
00:34:38,150 --> 00:34:41,028
The fastest of the fastest
of Jamaican sprinters

502
00:34:41,153 --> 00:34:43,155
Go to Olympics
Fight for Jamaica

503
00:35:23,235 --> 00:35:29,074
Welcome to Calgary, Alberta, Canada,
home of the 1988 Winter Olympic Games.

504
00:35:29,199 --> 00:35:32,285
- This is it.
- We hope you all enjoy your stay.

505
00:36:07,403 --> 00:36:10,489
Sanka, man, what you smokin'?

506
00:36:10,614 --> 00:36:13,242
I'm not smokin'.
I'm breathin'.

507
00:36:16,078 --> 00:36:19,915
- All right, fellas,
this is us. Let's go!
- Move! Let's go! Move!

508
00:36:20,040 --> 00:36:22,334
- Aah! Me first!
- What's the matter? You guys cold?

509
00:36:23,919 --> 00:36:27,131
It's not so much the heat; it's
the humidity that'll kill you.

510
00:37:13,259 --> 00:37:15,928
Excuse me, do you know where
you can register for bobsled?

511
00:37:21,517 --> 00:37:23,895
Do you know where you
register for bobsled?

512
00:37:29,734 --> 00:37:31,610
- See you.
- I'll see you around.

513
00:37:34,154 --> 00:37:37,199
- Okay, Mike, good to see you again.
- Ja?

514
00:37:37,324 --> 00:37:39,201
- Take care. All the best.
- Ja? Okay, ja.

515
00:37:41,161 --> 00:37:44,122
- Can I help you?
- Yeah, I'd like to
register for the tryouts.

516
00:37:44,247 --> 00:37:47,083
- What country?
- Uh, Jamaica.

517
00:37:47,209 --> 00:37:48,877
What country?

518
00:37:49,002 --> 00:37:50,503
Jamaica.

519
00:37:53,965 --> 00:37:58,178
Well, what do you know?
A Jamaican bobsled team.

520
00:37:58,303 --> 00:38:00,221
Okay, here it is.

521
00:38:00,347 --> 00:38:04,392
Uh, it says here your qualifying run
will be held on the evening of the 10th.

522
00:38:04,517 --> 00:38:07,437
Your judges will be Shindler,
Gremmer and Kroychzech.

523
00:38:07,562 --> 00:38:11,441
- I know Kroychzech. He's a good guy.
- Yeah.

524
00:38:11,566 --> 00:38:16,904
In order to qualify, you must
complete the course safely in 1
minute, 2 seconds-flat or under.

525
00:38:17,029 --> 00:38:19,865
- Used to be a minute, five.
- Yeah.

526
00:38:19,990 --> 00:38:22,076
Times change.

527
00:38:27,414 --> 00:38:30,542
- Irv, is that you?
- Roger, how you doing?

528
00:38:30,668 --> 00:38:33,087
Hello, Kurt.
Been a long time.

529
00:38:35,881 --> 00:38:38,175
Obviously not long enough.

530
00:38:38,300 --> 00:38:42,262
- Hello, Larry.
- Jesus Christ, Irv.

531
00:38:42,388 --> 00:38:44,556
What the hell did you
do to yourself?

532
00:38:46,642 --> 00:38:49,186
- Don't worry about them, Irv.
- Roger, you got to do me a favor.

533
00:38:49,311 --> 00:38:51,730
- What?
- Please. You know that
revolving restaurant thing?

534
00:38:51,855 --> 00:38:53,732
- Yeah.
- Meet me there in half an hour.
- Half an hour?

535
00:38:53,856 --> 00:38:56,109
- Yeah. Please!
- Roger, come on!

536
00:38:56,234 --> 00:38:58,111
I'll try.

537
00:39:14,585 --> 00:39:18,297
- Thanks, Roger.
- Yeah, well... What's up, Irv?

538
00:39:18,423 --> 00:39:20,299
- How about a drink?
- No, I'm fine.

539
00:39:20,425 --> 00:39:22,844
- What's so important
that it couldn't wait?
- Want something to eat?

540
00:39:22,969 --> 00:39:25,763
- No, I'm fine!
- A salad or something?
- Irv!

541
00:39:28,141 --> 00:39:32,979
- I need a sled.
- You came all the way
to Calgary without a sled?

542
00:39:33,104 --> 00:39:36,481
I got 4,800 dollars.
I just need something competitive.

543
00:39:36,606 --> 00:39:39,693
- For five grand?
- I know you got something
lying around, Roger.

544
00:39:39,818 --> 00:39:41,695
- But, Irv...
- Anything.

545
00:39:41,820 --> 00:39:45,282
- You know I can't do that.
- Now, wait a minute, Roger.

546
00:39:45,407 --> 00:39:49,578
Remember when you were desperate
to make that last slot on the
'68 Grenoble team...

547
00:39:49,703 --> 00:39:51,705
and you pleaded with me
to talk to Kurt?

548
00:39:51,830 --> 00:39:54,124
Did I say, "Sorry, Roger,
I can't do it"?

549
00:39:54,249 --> 00:39:57,210
Come on, don't make me beg.

550
00:39:57,335 --> 00:40:00,213
Roger, it's me.

551
00:40:00,338 --> 00:40:03,508
All right, maybe I can get you
one of our practice sleds.

552
00:40:03,633 --> 00:40:06,511
You're a saint, you know that?
A saint! You haven't changed
a bit! You're still a saint!

553
00:40:06,636 --> 00:40:09,848
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, look, don't get
all mushy on me. Just tell me one thing.

554
00:40:09,973 --> 00:40:14,686
Is this whole thing a big joke,
or do you really expect these
Jamaicans to qualify?

555
00:40:14,811 --> 00:40:18,898
Not only are they going to
qualify, they're going to
turn some heads doing it.

556
00:40:19,023 --> 00:40:24,195
Listen, three of these guys
can run the hundred in under ten-flat.

557
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:26,739
I don't care who you are,
that's lightning.

558
00:40:26,864 --> 00:40:30,034
Yeah, but can lightning
run on ice?

559
00:40:49,053 --> 00:40:50,930
No problem, man.

560
00:40:55,017 --> 00:40:56,894
God!

561
00:41:04,859 --> 00:41:08,571
Irv, these special shoes
aren't very effective.

562
00:41:19,540 --> 00:41:22,085
Grip with your toes!

563
00:41:22,210 --> 00:41:24,837
All right, you sugar-coated
track stars!

564
00:41:24,963 --> 00:41:28,591
Move out and let the ice rasta
show you how it's done.

565
00:41:30,677 --> 00:41:34,430
- Yeah. Like that, yeah. Good.
- Hey, fellas!

566
00:41:34,555 --> 00:41:37,266
- Look at my progress.
- Stop touching me!

567
00:41:45,774 --> 00:41:50,445
All right, fellas, that's it!
Let's get off the ice before practice.

568
00:41:50,570 --> 00:41:53,573
- What practice?
- That practice.

569
00:42:09,089 --> 00:42:10,966
That's right.

570
00:42:14,720 --> 00:42:16,596
Good team this year.

571
00:42:54,633 --> 00:42:59,388
Ein, zwei, drei!

572
00:44:16,797 --> 00:44:19,800
Oh, man, you should see this
on the hill.

573
00:44:19,925 --> 00:44:22,427
- It's like a miracle.
- What's "Schweiz"?

574
00:44:22,552 --> 00:44:26,306
- No, man! Swiss!
- This is the real thing, man.

575
00:44:26,431 --> 00:44:28,599
Gentlemen...

576
00:44:28,724 --> 00:44:31,852
I'd like to introduce you to
the newest member of our team.

577
00:44:36,816 --> 00:44:42,280
Um, you won't believe what I
had to go through to get us
a sled in such good shape.

578
00:44:42,405 --> 00:44:44,198
Uh...

579
00:44:45,574 --> 00:44:48,202
If we're going to make it
into the Olympics...

580
00:44:48,327 --> 00:44:51,539
this is the boat that's
going to take us there.

581
00:44:51,664 --> 00:44:54,125
Well, I'm... I'm told
she's actually quite fast.

582
00:44:57,128 --> 00:44:59,839
I, uh, know she's not
much to look at...

583
00:44:59,964 --> 00:45:03,467
- but, uh...
- Shh! She's beautiful!

584
00:45:15,854 --> 00:45:19,899
All coaches must sign teams in
before approaching bob run.

585
00:45:41,129 --> 00:45:43,006
Here we go.

586
00:45:45,300 --> 00:45:47,177
Let's go! Let's go!

587
00:45:49,179 --> 00:45:51,054
- Hold on a minute.
- All right, come on.

588
00:45:53,265 --> 00:45:55,142
Here we go.

589
00:46:13,160 --> 00:46:15,871
Ah. This is good.

590
00:46:19,166 --> 00:46:21,335
Okay, this is it.

591
00:46:21,460 --> 00:46:24,713
- Everybody climb in.
- Hold up. I don't understand.

592
00:46:24,838 --> 00:46:27,925
- We're not going to push start?
- No, we're going to push start
next time.

593
00:46:28,050 --> 00:46:30,385
For your first run, I'm just going
to nudge you off, okay? Everybody in.

594
00:46:30,511 --> 00:46:32,386
Let's go, let's go.
Come on. Come on.

595
00:46:36,474 --> 00:46:38,726
- Don't touch me!
- Hey, Baldy, get off my foot!

596
00:46:38,851 --> 00:46:40,728
- Don't touch me!
- Here you go. Come on.

597
00:46:40,853 --> 00:46:45,233
Hey, Blitzer, why don't you put
some training wheels on that sled?

598
00:46:46,484 --> 00:46:48,861
That's funny. Very funny.

599
00:46:48,986 --> 00:46:51,239
You want to kiss my egg?

600
00:46:51,364 --> 00:46:54,075
I'm not kissing no egg.

601
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:56,077
- Suit yourself.
- Now, listen up, fellas.

602
00:46:56,202 --> 00:47:00,081
- I don't want you to worry
about looking good out there.
- Ah, Blitzie.

603
00:47:00,206 --> 00:47:03,209
You going to tuck them in too?

604
00:47:03,334 --> 00:47:06,295
Hey... Seeming to you
like nobody likes us?

605
00:47:06,420 --> 00:47:10,550
We're different. People are always
afraid of what's different.

606
00:47:10,675 --> 00:47:12,927
Hey, Jamaica.

607
00:47:13,052 --> 00:47:16,554
Watch out for number 12 turn.
It's scary, huh?

608
00:47:18,473 --> 00:47:21,142
- What's his problem?
- He's Josef Grool.

609
00:47:21,268 --> 00:47:23,103
He's one of the best drivers
in the world.

610
00:47:23,228 --> 00:47:25,605
Yeah, he's one of the biggest
assholes in the world too.

611
00:47:25,730 --> 00:47:27,899
Well, don't listen to him.
You listen to me.

612
00:47:28,024 --> 00:47:30,110
Derice, right here.
You got it?

613
00:47:30,235 --> 00:47:34,781
Remember, keep your hands soft
and your mind clear.

614
00:47:34,906 --> 00:47:38,451
- High in, low out. What is it?
- High in, low out.

615
00:47:38,576 --> 00:47:41,496
All right, put your helmets on,
everybody! Let's go!

616
00:47:41,621 --> 00:47:44,624
Here we go! Come on!
Helmets on!

617
00:47:46,543 --> 00:47:48,086
- Hey, Coach.
- Yeah?

618
00:47:48,211 --> 00:47:51,339
I can't get my helmet on!
Oh, thanks, Coach.

619
00:47:51,464 --> 00:47:54,134
- That's what I'm here for.
- Oh. Coach?

620
00:47:54,259 --> 00:47:56,927
- Yeah.
- I got to go, you know.

621
00:47:57,052 --> 00:48:00,472
- Hold it.
- Hold it?
- Hold it.
- Hold it?

622
00:48:00,597 --> 00:48:05,352
- Yeah, hold it!
- B-But, Coach, I can't hold it!
We're not bobsledding yet.

623
00:48:05,477 --> 00:48:09,106
- Oh, yes, we are.
- Coach! Coach!

624
00:48:11,567 --> 00:48:13,444
Coach!

625
00:48:15,154 --> 00:48:16,655
Coach! Coach!

626
00:48:20,409 --> 00:48:22,286
Bob in track.

627
00:48:26,623 --> 00:48:28,500
Coach!

628
00:48:35,799 --> 00:48:39,135
Slow down! Oh! Slow it down!
Slow down! Slow it down!

629
00:48:39,260 --> 00:48:42,513
Oh, my god! Oh!
Oh, Derice! Oh, Derice!

630
00:48:42,638 --> 00:48:46,809
I hate you!
I hate you! I hate you!

631
00:48:46,934 --> 00:48:48,227
Whoa!

632
00:48:59,989 --> 00:49:01,908
Sanka, you dead?

633
00:49:03,284 --> 00:49:05,745
Yeah, man.

634
00:49:05,870 --> 00:49:08,164
Well, you can pee now.

635
00:49:10,082 --> 00:49:12,210
Ohh. Too late.

636
00:49:14,962 --> 00:49:16,839
This is embarrassing.

637
00:49:21,718 --> 00:49:25,472
Man, shut down that
hot plate, fool.

638
00:49:25,597 --> 00:49:27,849
Those bananas are stinking
like a dead dog.

639
00:49:27,974 --> 00:49:32,062
Back off! Back off, you eight-ball!
This is my mama's secret recipe.

640
00:49:32,187 --> 00:49:35,899
And I hope you don't mind keeping quiet
while I catch up on my reading.

641
00:49:36,024 --> 00:49:39,611
What are you talking about, reading?
This is a children's book.

642
00:49:39,736 --> 00:49:42,072
- Oh, is that so?
- Yes, that's so.

643
00:49:42,197 --> 00:49:45,575
Well, if it's a children's book,
that means it's too advanced
for the likes of you.

644
00:49:45,700 --> 00:49:49,579
What are you trying to say, that I'm
not smarter than a little child?

645
00:49:49,704 --> 00:49:51,873
No, what I am saying to you...

646
00:49:51,998 --> 00:49:56,628
is that you are the kind of
club-totin', raw meat-eatin',
me-Tarzan-you-Jane-in'...

647
00:49:56,753 --> 00:50:01,632
big, bald bubblehead that
can only count to ten if he's
barefoot or wearing sandals.

648
00:50:01,757 --> 00:50:04,718
Say whatever it is
that you want...

649
00:50:04,843 --> 00:50:08,013
'cause you're just like every
other fool on the island.

650
00:50:10,015 --> 00:50:14,603
You're going nowhere, Sanka,
and you're thrilled to death about it.

651
00:50:16,063 --> 00:50:19,733
But you see me?
You see me?

652
00:50:19,858 --> 00:50:23,445
I'm different,
'cause I know exactly...

653
00:50:23,571 --> 00:50:25,656
where I'm going...

654
00:50:25,781 --> 00:50:31,412
and after I, Yul Brenner, win
the Olympics and become famous...

655
00:50:31,537 --> 00:50:33,414
I'm going to leave the island...

656
00:50:34,748 --> 00:50:37,626
and live right down there.

657
00:50:42,714 --> 00:50:45,091
What are you laughing about?

658
00:50:45,216 --> 00:50:47,677
- What are you laughing about?
- That's Buckingham Palace.

659
00:50:49,929 --> 00:50:53,266
You plan on living there, you're
going to have to marry the Queen.

660
00:50:53,391 --> 00:50:56,477
Yul, that's where
the Queen of England lives.

661
00:51:01,441 --> 00:51:05,528
Face it, Yul Brenner... You can
start calling yourself Madonna...

662
00:51:05,653 --> 00:51:10,450
but you're still going to end up
in an outhouse shanty like every
other dock-working nobody.

663
00:51:10,575 --> 00:51:13,995
- Mm, says who?
- Says me, rich boy.
What do you know about it?

664
00:51:14,120 --> 00:51:17,206
Well, I know my father
started off in a one-room hut.

665
00:51:17,332 --> 00:51:22,003
- Now he lives in one of the
biggest homes in Kingston.
- Well, he ain't your father.

666
00:51:22,128 --> 00:51:24,629
He doesn't have to be.

667
00:51:24,755 --> 00:51:28,008
All he has to do is know what
he wants and work hard for it.

668
00:51:28,133 --> 00:51:31,386
And if he wants it bad enough,
he'll get it.

669
00:51:32,637 --> 00:51:36,349
Look, believe me, Sanka...

670
00:51:36,475 --> 00:51:39,311
the more Yul Brenners we got
making it in this world...

671
00:51:39,436 --> 00:51:44,357
the better off this world will
be, especially for Jamaicans.

672
00:52:00,499 --> 00:52:02,959
Go ahead, Yul Brenner.

673
00:52:03,085 --> 00:52:04,960
Go get your palace.

674
00:52:18,182 --> 00:52:20,059
Move! Move!

675
00:52:21,435 --> 00:52:23,312
Bob in track.

676
00:52:27,608 --> 00:52:30,402
What do you have in there,
a baby?

677
00:52:34,073 --> 00:52:36,992
- I can't believe you're still cold, man.
- Cold?

678
00:52:37,117 --> 00:52:40,412
I'm freezing my royal
Rastafarian nay-nays off!

679
00:52:40,538 --> 00:52:42,748
All right, we're up!
Let's go, guys, this is it!

680
00:52:42,873 --> 00:52:44,750
Give me that!

681
00:52:44,875 --> 00:52:50,088
Okay, now, this is our first real push
start. But don't worry about it, okay?

