01:09:39,446 --> 01:09:42,783
- To the messenger.
- To the messenger.
- To the messenger.

916
01:09:48,789 --> 01:09:52,292
We are officially
disqualified.

917
01:10:03,262 --> 01:10:06,806
Excuse me, gentlemen. Kurt,
I really have to talk to you.

918
01:10:06,931 --> 01:10:10,184
Excuse me, Irv. I've
nothing to say to you.

919
01:10:10,309 --> 01:10:12,186
Yes, you do.

920
01:10:12,311 --> 01:10:14,981
- I want to know why
you disqualified my guys.
- As you were told...

921
01:10:15,106 --> 01:10:18,943
your team must compete in
an international race in order
to qualify for the Olympics.

922
01:10:19,068 --> 01:10:20,945
But in an Olympic year...

923
01:10:21,070 --> 01:10:23,406
the qualifiers count
as an international race.

924
01:10:23,531 --> 01:10:26,033
That may have been true
in past Olympic years...

925
01:10:26,159 --> 01:10:29,495
but this year, the Alliance
decided to change its policy.

926
01:10:29,620 --> 01:10:32,540
Oh, please!
Change its policy?

927
01:10:32,665 --> 01:10:36,753
The Alliance has the right to do
whatever they feel is in the
best interest of the sport.

928
01:10:36,878 --> 01:10:41,591
We must also be concerned about
the potential for embarrassment.

929
01:10:41,716 --> 01:10:43,885
Oh, forgive me.
I didn't realize...

930
01:10:44,010 --> 01:10:47,096
that four black guys in
a bobsled could make you blush.

931
01:10:47,221 --> 01:10:49,806
I think we've heard enough.

932
01:10:49,931 --> 01:10:53,560
Come on, Kurt. What you're doin'
is wrong and you know it.

933
01:10:53,685 --> 01:10:55,562
Now, if this is about
you and me...

934
01:10:55,687 --> 01:10:58,648
then let's get it straight
right now.

935
01:10:58,773 --> 01:11:02,652
All right, 16 years ago, I made
the biggest mistake of my life.

936
01:11:02,777 --> 01:11:06,072
I cheated.
I was stupid.

937
01:11:06,198 --> 01:11:09,951
I embarrassed myself,
my family...

938
01:11:10,076 --> 01:11:13,330
my teammates,
my country and my coach.

939
01:11:15,499 --> 01:11:18,543
If it's revenge you want,
take it.

940
01:11:18,668 --> 01:11:21,713
Go ahead.
Disqualify me. Banish me.

941
01:11:21,838 --> 01:11:23,757
Do whatever you want,
but do it to me.

942
01:11:23,882 --> 01:11:28,345
It was me who let you down,
Kurt. It wasn't my guys.

943
01:11:28,470 --> 01:11:30,513
They've done everything you've
asked of them, and they did it...

944
01:11:30,638 --> 01:11:34,725
with all of you
laughing in their face.

945
01:11:34,850 --> 01:11:38,187
Hell, it doesn't matter
if they come in first or 50th.

946
01:11:38,312 --> 01:11:41,607
Those guys have earned the right
to represent their country.

947
01:11:41,732 --> 01:11:43,609
They've earned the right...

948
01:11:43,734 --> 01:11:47,446
to march into that stadium
and wave their nation's flag.

949
01:11:47,571 --> 01:11:49,615
That's the single
greatest honor...

950
01:11:49,740 --> 01:11:51,617
an athlete
could ever have.

951
01:11:53,911 --> 01:11:56,455
That's what the Olympics
are about.

952
01:11:58,499 --> 01:12:00,709
Sixteen years ago,
I forgot that.

953
01:12:02,294 --> 01:12:04,171
Don't you go
and do the same.

954
01:12:08,175 --> 01:12:10,177
Sorry if I interrupted
your meeting.

955
01:12:24,190 --> 01:12:26,818
Hello. Yes?

956
01:12:30,405 --> 01:12:32,282
Yeah.

957
01:12:34,117 --> 01:12:35,994
Right. Goodbye.

958
01:12:39,914 --> 01:12:43,418
- What?
- That was the Alliance.

959
01:12:43,543 --> 01:12:45,920
- God.
- What did they say?

960
01:12:47,380 --> 01:12:49,298
Oh, they said
we're back in.

961
01:12:52,801 --> 01:12:54,845
Yes! Yes! Yes!

962
01:13:06,148 --> 01:13:08,775
And a lot is expected
of the Italian team.

963
01:13:08,900 --> 01:13:11,194
Did I miss it?
Did I miss it?

964
01:13:11,319 --> 01:13:14,281
No, child.
You didn't miss a thing.

965
01:13:14,406 --> 01:13:17,117
...of Jamaica made it
all the way here to Calgary...

966
01:13:17,242 --> 01:13:19,244
to compete
in the bobsled event.

967
01:13:19,369 --> 01:13:22,372
Their flag bearer is
the sled captain Derice Bannock.

968
01:13:22,497 --> 01:13:25,709
Derice's father, Ben Bannock, was
a gold medalist in the 200 meters...

969
01:13:25,834 --> 01:13:28,545
at the Summer Olympic games
over 20 years ago.

970
01:13:28,670 --> 01:13:32,215
And perhaps there's gold in
two generations of this family.

971
01:13:32,340 --> 01:13:35,217
That's quite a story.
The Jamaican bobsled team.

972
01:13:35,342 --> 01:13:39,054
It's a beautiful afternoon in Calgary,
and there is a lot more coming up.

973
01:13:39,180 --> 01:13:41,265
So stay tuned for
more exciting coverage...

974
01:13:41,390 --> 01:13:44,810
of the opening ceremonies
of the 15th Winter Olympiad...

975
01:13:44,935 --> 01:13:47,396
from Calgary,
Alberta, Canada.

976
01:13:54,320 --> 01:13:56,947
Gentlemen, let's go
check into our new home.

977
01:13:57,072 --> 01:13:58,949
Come on, Junior.

978
01:14:06,081 --> 01:14:07,958
Junior! Hey!

979
01:14:13,088 --> 01:14:14,965
Junior.

980
01:14:18,218 --> 01:14:20,720
Now a lot of coaches would be
giving you one of those, uh...

981
01:14:20,845 --> 01:14:23,515
"Win one for the Gipper"
speeches.

982
01:14:23,640 --> 01:14:26,643
I'm not good at that stuff.
Instead, I thought I'd, uh...

983
01:14:26,768 --> 01:14:29,395
lead you in a psalm
of inspiration.

984
01:14:29,521 --> 01:14:31,397
Let's bow our heads.

985
01:14:31,523 --> 01:14:33,525
Who's the "Gipper"?

986
01:14:33,650 --> 01:14:38,530
Our Father who art in Calgary,
bobsled be Thy name.

987
01:14:38,655 --> 01:14:41,658
Thy kingdom come,
gold medals won...

988
01:14:41,783 --> 01:14:44,035
on Earth as it is
in turn seven.

989
01:14:44,160 --> 01:14:46,955
With liberty and justice
for Jamaica and Haile Selassie.

990
01:14:47,080 --> 01:14:49,499
- Amen.
- All right!

991
01:14:49,624 --> 01:14:51,918
- Yes!
- Respect.

992
01:14:52,043 --> 01:14:53,920
- All right.
- Jah Rastafari.

993
01:15:04,388 --> 01:15:06,265
Junior.

994
01:15:10,936 --> 01:15:12,813
Now you listen to me, boy.

995
01:15:15,274 --> 01:15:17,651
You might not have done
what you were asked...

996
01:15:17,776 --> 01:15:20,445
but you will do
what you're told.

997
01:15:20,570 --> 01:15:23,156
- You're coming home.
- Yeah, but, Father,
you know I just want...

998
01:15:23,282 --> 01:15:25,492
But nothing.

999
01:15:25,617 --> 01:15:27,786
I didn't send you
to the finest school...

1000
01:15:27,911 --> 01:15:31,999
for you to go around
sliding on your backside.

1001
01:15:32,124 --> 01:15:34,918
- You must be mad.
- Yeah, but the team needs me.

1002
01:15:35,043 --> 01:15:37,587
I don't want to hear
any more of it.

1003
01:15:38,964 --> 01:15:40,923
Go and get your things.

1004
01:15:52,643 --> 01:15:54,520
I'll wait in the lobby.

1005
01:16:00,151 --> 01:16:02,778
Pride. Power.

1006
01:16:06,365 --> 01:16:10,411
Father, when you look
at me, what do you see?

1007
01:16:10,536 --> 01:16:12,663
I don't have time
for games, Junior.

1008
01:16:12,788 --> 01:16:14,707
Tell me what ya see!

1009
01:16:14,832 --> 01:16:17,376
Please.

1010
01:16:17,501 --> 01:16:19,462
All right, I'll tell you
what I see.

1011
01:16:19,587 --> 01:16:21,463
I see a lost little boy...

1012
01:16:21,588 --> 01:16:25,550
who's lucky to have a father
who knows what's best for him.

1013
01:16:25,675 --> 01:16:29,512
No, no, no, no. You don't know
what's best for me, Father.

1014
01:16:29,637 --> 01:16:32,807
I am not a lost
little boy, Father.

1015
01:16:32,932 --> 01:16:34,809
I am a man.

1016
01:16:34,934 --> 01:16:37,020
And I'm an Olympian.

1017
01:16:39,898 --> 01:16:41,941
I'm stayin' right here.

1018
01:16:53,787 --> 01:16:56,748
Hey, Junior Bevil.

1019
01:16:56,873 --> 01:16:58,917
You're a badass mother.

1020
01:17:15,390 --> 01:17:18,769
- Here, I-I got a couple.
- I like this one. Yes.

1021
01:17:24,399 --> 01:17:27,736
O Canada, indeed. This is Al Trautwig
along with John Morgan.

1022
01:17:27,861 --> 01:17:30,489
We're live at Olympic Park,
the brand-new bobsledding venue...

1023
01:17:30,614 --> 01:17:32,866
just a few miles outside
of downtown Calgary.

1024
01:17:32,991 --> 01:17:35,327
Everybody, shut up.
It's starting.

1025
01:17:35,452 --> 01:17:38,622
...extremely intense, exciting
competition for the next three days.

1026
01:17:47,255 --> 01:17:50,466
I am feeling very Olympic
today. How about you?

1027
01:17:53,928 --> 01:17:56,764
Uh, this sport, as we well know,
us made up of athletes...

1028
01:17:56,889 --> 01:17:59,475
who go to the edge and sometimes
beyond, and it is why we believe...

1029
01:17:59,600 --> 01:18:02,728
the next three days is going to be
extremely competitive and exciting.

1030
01:18:02,853 --> 01:18:06,148
And already, John, on day one,
we're starting things off
with a gold medal favorite.

1031
01:18:06,274 --> 01:18:09,318
Well, the Swiss were fortunate enough
to draw number one in the competition.

1032
01:18:09,443 --> 01:18:11,696
We gotta make them the odds-on
favorite to win the gold.

1033
01:18:11,821 --> 01:18:15,032
But the East Germans, they're comin'
off the gold medal win in 1984.

1034
01:18:15,157 --> 01:18:17,493
The Canadians, it's their home track.
You gotta favor them too.

1035
01:18:17,618 --> 01:18:19,954
And they've been doin'
very well in practice all week.

1036
01:18:27,210 --> 01:18:30,130
Eins, zwei, drei.

1037
01:18:36,177 --> 01:18:39,097
One! Two! Three! Go!

1038
01:18:53,194 --> 01:18:55,280
- Eighty miles an hour or close to it.
- You know, Al,

1039
01:18:55,405 --> 01:18:58,033
I'm lookin' at the times here, and
the course is gettin' extremely fast.

1040
01:18:58,158 --> 01:19:00,243
And I was worried about that Austrian
team's safety in that last big...

1041
01:19:00,368 --> 01:19:03,288
180-degree whiparound that draws
four G's of force on the athletes.

1042
01:19:03,413 --> 01:19:06,791
Well, if you were worried about
them, what are you thinking
about our last and next team?

1043
01:19:06,916 --> 01:19:10,294
Yes, it certainly seems
strange that surrounded by
the ice and snow of Calgary,

1044
01:19:10,419 --> 01:19:14,298
we are about to watch a team
from the tiny island of Jamaica.

1045
01:19:16,508 --> 01:19:19,303
- From Jamaica!
- Quite a story for them
to even get here.

1046
01:19:19,428 --> 01:19:22,681
They came out of nowhere. And
you know, there's a lot of teams
up here on top of the hill...

1047
01:19:22,806 --> 01:19:25,601
that sort of feel the Jamaicans
don't belong here.

1048
01:19:33,025 --> 01:19:35,736
- Hey! Hey!
- Hey, what are you doin', man?

1049
01:19:35,861 --> 01:19:38,739
- What are you doing?
- That's what the Swiss do
to psych themselves up.

1050
01:19:38,864 --> 01:19:42,409
They also make them little pocketknives,
too, but I don't see you doin' that.

1051
01:19:42,534 --> 01:19:45,913
All right, guys, we're up. Come on. Hey,
knock it off. Knock it off, will ya?

1052
01:19:46,038 --> 01:19:48,248
Okay. Let's go.
Come on.

1053
01:19:48,373 --> 01:19:52,251
Take your start positions.
Remember, we don't have to win
the gold in the first day.

1054
01:19:52,376 --> 01:19:54,462
- It's just like any other run.
- Except this time...

1055
01:19:54,587 --> 01:19:56,547
100 million people watching.

1056
01:19:56,672 --> 01:19:59,592
Derice, did you forget
something? Thank you.

1057
01:19:59,717 --> 01:20:01,636
- Ready.
- Ready.

1058
01:20:01,761 --> 01:20:03,387
- Ready.
- Ready.

1059
01:20:03,513 --> 01:20:07,892
Eins, zwei, drei.

1060
01:20:09,185 --> 01:20:12,271
Go! Go, go, go, go! Go!

1061
01:20:14,732 --> 01:20:18,027
- Get in! Get in!
- As the Jamaican team attempts
its first ever...

1062
01:20:18,152 --> 01:20:20,613
winter Olympic event,
and look at this.

1063
01:20:20,738 --> 01:20:24,158
They've gotta get into that sled.
I've never seen anything like this.

1064
01:20:24,283 --> 01:20:27,370
I know it's not funny,
but how embarrassing.

1065
01:20:27,495 --> 01:20:30,206
Now, thank goodness. For
a minute, I didn't think they'd
ever get all four of them in.

1066
01:20:30,331 --> 01:20:32,916
And that could've been
a disaster.

1067
01:20:33,041 --> 01:20:35,627
C-Come on!

1068
01:20:35,752 --> 01:20:37,629
Well, most importantly here,
when you do get in the sled...

1069
01:20:37,754 --> 01:20:40,131
you have to get in with catlike
movements, get in, get relaxed.

1070
01:20:40,257 --> 01:20:44,553
Ooh, look at that high line at
Omega! He bounces off the wall,
ricochets like a pinball.

1071
01:20:44,678 --> 01:20:47,848
You know, the driver here,
Derice Bannock, looks like
the sled's really drivin' him.

1072
01:20:47,973 --> 01:20:52,477
- That fool better watch his mouth.
- He better watch more than that.

1073
01:20:52,602 --> 01:20:56,356
This is the time when this team
may be thinking, "This may not
have been such a great idea."

1074
01:20:56,481 --> 01:20:58,525
Their heads are bouncing around.
This is amazing.

1075
01:20:58,650 --> 01:21:00,986
Like rag dolls as they come
through the finish...

1076
01:21:01,111 --> 01:21:04,155
at a time of 58.04...

1077
01:21:04,281 --> 01:21:06,908
which will be good enough
for last place.

1078
01:21:13,414 --> 01:21:18,711
You choked. It was yours for
the taking, and you choked.

1079
01:21:18,836 --> 01:21:21,380
You were ready,
and ya choked.

1080
01:21:22,881 --> 01:21:25,384
Well, maybe we should
go over the turns again?

1081
01:21:25,509 --> 01:21:27,720
You know the turns.

1082
01:21:27,845 --> 01:21:30,264
You know everything there is
to know about this sport.

1083
01:21:30,389 --> 01:21:33,142
I'll tell you somethin'.
You had all better figure out...

1084
01:21:33,267 --> 01:21:36,020
how to stay loose out there.

1085
01:21:36,145 --> 01:21:39,690
That's somethin'
I can't help you with.

1086
01:21:39,815 --> 01:21:42,484
I'll see you tomorrow
on the hill.

1087
01:21:57,081 --> 01:21:59,834
You know, when the Swiss
want to get relaxed...

1088
01:21:59,959 --> 01:22:02,920
Will you shut up
about the damn Swiss?

1089
01:22:03,046 --> 01:22:07,425
I mean, it was all that "eins,
zwei, drei" nonsense that got us
all nervous in the first place.

1090
01:22:07,550 --> 01:22:10,428
Hey, man, look here. I'm just tryin'
to get us off on the right foot.

1091
01:22:10,553 --> 01:22:13,431
Well, the right foot for us
is not the Swiss foot.

1092
01:22:13,556 --> 01:22:17,894
I mean, come on, Derice. We
can't be copyin' nobody else's
style. We have our own style.

1093
01:22:18,019 --> 01:22:20,271
Kissin' an egg
is no kind of style.

1094
01:22:20,396 --> 01:22:23,691
It's the Olympics here.
It's no stupid pushcart derby.

1095
01:22:29,030 --> 01:22:31,157
Let me tell ya
somethin', Rasta.

1096
01:22:31,282 --> 01:22:34,243
I didn't come up here to forget
who I am and where I come from.

1097
01:22:34,369 --> 01:22:38,497
And neither did I. I'm just
tryin' to be the best I can be.

1098
01:22:38,622 --> 01:22:42,084
So am I. And the best
I can be is Jamaican.

1099
01:22:48,423 --> 01:22:54,262
Look. Derice, I've known you since Julie
Jeffries asked to see your ding-a-ling.

1100
01:22:54,387 --> 01:22:57,015
And I'm telling you
as a friend...

1101
01:22:57,140 --> 01:22:59,768
if we look Jamaican,
walk Jamaican...

1102
01:22:59,893 --> 01:23:02,479
talk Jamaican
and is Jamaican...

1103
01:23:02,604 --> 01:23:05,941
then we sure as hell
better bobsled Jamaican.

1104
01:23:13,740 --> 01:23:15,784
Greetings from Jamaica

1105
01:23:15,909 --> 01:23:18,410
'Nuff people will say
you know they can't believe

1106
01:23:18,536 --> 01:23:20,830
Jamaica we have
a bobsled team

1107
01:23:20,955 --> 01:23:23,124
'Nuff people say
you know they can't believe

1108
01:23:23,249 --> 01:23:25,292
Jamaica we have
a bobsled team

1109
01:23:25,417 --> 01:23:27,753
We have the one Derice
and the one Junior

1110
01:23:27,878 --> 01:23:30,131
- Thank you.
- Yul Brenner and the man Sanka

1111
01:23:30,256 --> 01:23:32,758
The fastest of the fastest
of Jamaican sprinters

1112
01:23:32,883 --> 01:23:34,844
Respect to the man
Irv Blitzer

1113
01:23:34,969 --> 01:23:37,221
- All right, gentlemen, this is it.
- Respect.

1114
01:23:37,346 --> 01:23:39,306
- Respect! Whoo!
- All right.
- Let's go!

1115
01:23:39,431 --> 01:23:43,227
We now come to the second chance for
the four intrepid men from Jamaica.

1116
01:23:43,352 --> 01:23:46,188
- What do they have to do, John?
- In reality, Al, I don't think
the Jamaicans...

1117
01:23:46,313 --> 01:23:48,816
- have any chance of winning a medal.
- Dear God!

1118
01:23:48,941 --> 01:23:51,902
Just let them be better
than yesterday.

1119
01:23:56,282 --> 01:23:58,325
- Ready.
- Ready.

1120
01:23:58,449 --> 01:24:01,202
Feel the rhythm!
Feel the rhyme!

1121
01:24:01,327 --> 01:24:03,997
Get on up!
It's bobsled time!

1122
01:24:04,122 --> 01:24:07,458
Cool runnings!

1123
01:24:07,584 --> 01:24:10,670
Bob in track.

1124
01:24:10,795 --> 01:24:14,299
That's a hair faster than the
Swiss. Boy, that's a real big
difference from yesterday.

1125
01:24:14,424 --> 01:24:16,467
Well, this is an absolute shock
in the making. Yesterday...

1126
01:24:16,593 --> 01:24:18,845
- they were falling down
almost at the start.
- Yes!

1127
01:24:18,970 --> 01:24:22,056
Now they slide into place. Yesterday,
their heads were bobbing everywhere.

1128
01:24:22,181 --> 01:24:25,476
Today, they're
almost in unison.

1129
01:24:37,822 --> 01:24:40,073
- Can this really be happening?
- Boy, what a difference!

1130
01:24:40,198 --> 01:24:44,119
Flying through the Omega,
looking possessed here. It's not
the same team we saw yesterday.

1131
01:24:44,244 --> 01:24:47,205
- Where did these guys come from?
- Jamaica!

1132
01:24:54,588 --> 01:24:57,591
Wow! 56.53!

1133
01:24:57,716 --> 01:25:00,093
Whoo-hoo! Yes! Yes!

1134
01:25:00,218 --> 01:25:03,096
- Did you hear that time? Yes!
- Yeah.

1135
01:25:12,814 --> 01:25:14,733
- That moves them up into 8th place.
- Watch out, world.

1136
01:25:14,858 --> 01:25:17,569
The Jamaicans are coming.

